            <title>CalStar Opens Mississippi Plant</title>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;
	CalStar Products recently opened a new 100,000-square-foot manufacturing plant in Columbus, Mississippi. The facility, which is CalStar&amp;#39;s second, sits on 23 acres in the Golden Triangle Industrial Park.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The company will run two lines at the plant, each utilizing CalStar&amp;#39;s sustainable manufacturing process. The dry-cast line will manufacture all of CalStar&amp;#39;s brick and Thru-Wall units as well as Holland pavers, while the semi-automated wet-cast line will produce cast stone trim and accent pieces.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;quot;Columbus has proven to be the ideal second home for CalStar, with a central location in the South, a talented pool of labor and strong local business leadership,&amp;quot; says CalStar CEO Joel Rood. &amp;quot;As CalStar continues its rapid growth trajectory, we knew a second plant was key to expanding production and capabilities. We couldn&amp;#39;t be happier with our decision to open up in Columbus.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;quot;We are thrilled to welcome CalStar to the Golden Triangle,&amp;quot; says Joe Max Higgins, CEO of the Golden Triangle Development Link. &amp;quot;Their unique innovation and commitment to bring quality jobs to our community are two of the many reasons we&amp;rsquo;re looking forward to working with them as they make Lowndes County their home.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Incorporating up to 37 percent recycled content, CalStar masonry products eliminate the need for kiln-firing or the use of Portland cement to bind concrete masonry products. As a result, each product requires up to 81 percent less energy to make while emitting up to 84 percent less carbon dioxide.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	For more information, visit &lt;a href="http://www.calstarproducts.com"&gt;www.calstarproducts.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/noria/reliableplant/tags/green_manufacturing/~4/oxHSBO5gAPY" height="1" width="1" alt=""/&gt;</description>
            <a10:updated>2014-10-30T13:07:02-05:00</a10:updated>
            <a10:content type="text/html" src="http://reliableplant.com/Read/29936/calstar-mississippi-plant" />
        <feedburner:origLink>http://reliableplant.com/Read/29936/calstar-mississippi-plant</feedburner:origLink></item>
        <item>
            <guid isPermaLink="false">tag:noria.com,2010-06-10:publishing:magazines:rp:cd769a17-2363-4099-95e6-a30000a562a4</guid>
            <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/noria/reliableplant/tags/green_manufacturing/~3/4whnAYVBf4Y/zero-landfill-manufacturing</link>
